 emblem pictures consecrated to secular love experience, encapsulating some of the conventions of the sonnet sequences and having a strong influence on religious love literature.Each book is reproduced with critical and bibliographic introductions, translation of the poems and mottos, descriptions of the emblems, and indices to the visual and verbal components of the works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEmblem books, EnglishvIndexes. 0aEmblemszEnglandvEarly works to 1800. 0aEmblemszEnglandxEarly works to 1800vIndexes. 0aSymbolism in artxThemes, motivesvIndexes. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh1 aDaly, Peter M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDuer, Leslie T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilcox, Marv V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilcox, Mary V., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268118740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442681187423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442681187.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK